./.title: CEH - Practical Prep
./.body:
CEH - Practical Prep
My journey of CEH-Practical preparation and this can be used like cheatsheet during exam.

ceh-practical-prep/network-scanning/nmap.title: nmap
ceh-practical-prep/network-scanning/nmap.body:
nmap

Used for host discovery and network auditing
Usage:
nmap -sn ip/mask [nmap -sn 10.10.10.0/24 or nmap -sn 10.10.10.0-255] - ping scan for host discovery
nmap -sV ip - service discovery
nmap -p- -sV ip - service discovery all ports
nmap -p 80,443 -sV ip - service discovery for mentioned ports
nmap -A ip - os detection,script scanning and traceroute
nmap --script="some_script" ip - Run nmap specific nmap script
nmap --script smb-os-discovery.nse -p445 IP [SMB OS Detection]


Reference:
https://hackertarget.com/nmap-cheatsheet-a-quick-reference-guide/

ceh-practical-prep/network-scanning/netd.title: netdiscover
ceh-practical-prep/network-scanning/netd.body:
netdiscover

Discover live hosts
Usage:
netdiscover -i interfacename [ex:netdiscover -i eth0]

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/smb-enume.title: enum4linux
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/smb-enume.body:
enum4linux

Enumerate users, groups, shares, password policies on SMB.
Usage:
enum4linux -U IP [user enum]
enum4linux -S IP [shares enum]
enum4linux -M IP [machines enum]
enum4linux -a IP [All option]

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/smb-enume.title: smbclient
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/smb-enume.body:
smbclient

Tool to list shares, connect and transfer files from host to share and vice versa.
Usage:
smbclient -L //IP/ - List shares
smbclient -L //IP/ -U ''username%password"
smbclient //IP/sharepath [connect to share path]

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/netbios-e.title: NetBIOS Enumeration
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/netbios-e.body:
NetBIOS Enumeration

Scan Network for hosts:
nbtscan -r 192.168.0.1/24
nbtscan IP -vh [netbios enumeration with service detection in human readable format]
nmap -sV IP --script nbstat.nse -v


Reference:
https://null-byte.wonderhowto.com/how-to/enumerate-netbios-shares-with-nbtscan-nmap-scripting-engine-0193957/

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/nfs-enume.title: NFS Enumeration
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/nfs-enume.body:
NFS Enumeration

NFS allows file sharing across network as if they existed in local system.
NMAP Enumeration:
nmap --script=nfs-ls.nse,nfs-showmount.nse,nfs-statfs.nse -p 2049 IP


showmount Enumeration:
showmount IP (apt install nfs-common , if not work)


Mount NFS:
mount -t nfs -o ver=2 IP:/home /mnt/somedir


Reference:
https://book.hacktricks.xyz/pentesting/nfs-service-pentesting

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/hydra.htm.title: Hydra
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/hydra.htm.body:
Hydra

Tool to crack passwords of various web service and also system services/protocols such as SSH and FTP.
Usage:
hydra -l admin -P 1000_common_passwords.txt -s 8090 -f 192.168.1.4 http-get /get_camera_params.cgi [basic auth bruteforce]
hydra -l username -P wordlist.txt VICTIMIP http-post-form "/URLPATH:username=^USER^\&password=^PASS^:login error" -V
hydra -l root -P wordlist.txt -t 6 ssh://ip
hydra -l user -P wordlist.txt ftp://ip


Reference:
https://en.kali.tools/?p=220

ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/wpscan.ht.title: wpscan
ceh-practical-prep/enumeration/wpscan.ht.body:
wpscan

Scan Wordpress website for vulnerabilities, enumerate users, themes and plugins.
Usage:
wpscan --url example.com
wpscan --url example.com -e u [Enumerate users]
 wpscan --url example.com --passwords=rockyou.txt --usernames=admin,guest
wpscan --url example.com -e vt --api-token YOUR_TOKEN [Enumerate themes]
wpscan --url example.com -e vp --api-token YOUR_TOKEN [Enumerate plugins]

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/exiftoo.title: exiftool
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/exiftoo.body:
exiftool

Exiftool is a tool that allows you to view and edit image metadata
Commands:
exiftool inputfile

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/steghid.title: steghide
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/steghid.body:
steghide

Hide data and also decrypt data. Commonly used to hide text message inside image files(jpeg format), Sometimes data can be hidden in audio files too(ex:wav).
Commands
steghide command [ arguments ]
steghide extract -sf input_file -p password
steghide embed -cf input_file -ef Text_file_to_hide
steghide extract -sf inputfile -xf hiddenfiletoextract
steghide info inputfile

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/zsteg.h.title: Zsteg
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/zsteg.h.body:
Zsteg

Detect stegano-hidden data in PNG & BMP
Commands:
zsteg inputfilename
zsteg inputfilename specificpayload(ex:b1,bgr,lsb,xy)


Reference:
https://github.com/zed-0xff/zsteg

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/stegove.title: Stegoveritas
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/stegove.body:
Stegoveritas

StegoVeritas has default actions for most image types (gif,jpeg,png,tiff,bmp) and will attempt to run on any file.
Commands:
stegoveritas inputfile


Reference:
https://github.com/bannsec/stegoVeritas

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/spectro.title: Spectrograms
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/spectro.body:
Spectrograms

Spectrogram stegonography is the art of hiding hidden an image inside in an audio file's spectogram.
Open Sonic Visualizer in GUI, open file, Layers>Add Spectogram

ceh-practical-prep/steganography/stegsol.title: StegSolve
ceh-practical-prep/steganography/stegsol.body:
StegSolve

It is used to analyze images in different planes by taking off bits of the image.
Open stegsolve.jar, open image file, change planes and analyze.
Reference:
https://wiki.bi0s.in/steganography/stegsolve/

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: System Hacking,Cryptography & Bruteforce techniques
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
System Hacking,Cryptography & Bruteforce techniques

Kryptos -  The art of hiding data
Encoding - Just another form of representing data - base64,hex etc
Hash - one way function without secret key producing output of specific byte length, hard to reverse - MD5,SHA1 etc
Encryption - two way function, generally takes a password to produce encrypted text. Can be decrypted if password is known/brute-force. - RSA,AES etc
Example of Hashes.
Reference for bruteforce attacks.

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: Hashcat
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
Hashcat
Usage:

hashcat -m mode hashtocrack.txt pathtowordlist.txt 
hashcat -m mode hashtocrack.txt --show [To Show Cracked Password]

Reference:

Hash Modes

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: John The Ripper
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
John The Ripper
Usage:

john   --format="hash_format" --wordlist=""pathtowordlist.txt" hashfile.txt
john  --format=raw-sha256 --show  hashfile.txt [To show cracked password]
john hashfile.txt [if you can't identify hash or try automatically]

Reference:

Commonly used hash formats for john.

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: Rainbow Crack
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
Rainbow Crack

Rainbow table - map of pre-computed hash to password/secret.
Usage:
rcrack \ -h "hash"


Reference:
https://null-byte.wonderhowto.com/how-to/rainbow-tables-create-use-them-crack-passwords-0131470/

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: PwDump7
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
PwDump7

Dump NTLM password hashes of users in computer.
Usage:
PwDump7.exe >> hash.txt


Reference:
https://www.tarasco.org/security/pwdump_7/

ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.title: ophcrack
ceh-practical-prep/system-hacking-crypto.body:
ophcrack

Uses rainbow table to crack passwords provided in various formats such as NTLM,PwDump output etc
It can also be used in in Live CD environment to crack passwords without logging into windows.
Usage:
Better use GUI mode, load pwdump/input file.
Click tables and chose required table directory.
 Crack


Reference:
https://sourceforge.net/p/ophcrack/wiki/ophcrack%20Howto/

ceh-practical-prep/web-application-penet.title: sqlmap
ceh-practical-prep/web-application-penet.body:
sqlmap

Automated sql injection and database takeover tool.
Usage:
python sqlmap.py -u "http://www.target.com/vuln.php?id=1" [--dbs --tables --columns] (To Enumerate database or Tables or Columns)
python sqlmap.py -u "http://www.target.com/vuln.php?id=1" [-D dbname -T y=tblname -C colname] --dump (When you know DB name, table name or column name and dump the data)
python sqlmap -u "http://www.target.com/vuln.php?id=1" –method "POST" –data "postformdata" -D dbname -T tblname –dump
python sqlmap.py -r request.txt [--dbs --tables --columns] (If you hav e saved request from burp)

nikto
